n-surface-variant text-sm\",\"children\":\"Columbina's Truth suggests that the circus is a purgatorial system where characters forget but the world remembers. The three loops represent stages of memory erosion — each loop strips away more of the protagonist's identity until only instinct remains. The fourth door represents the boundary between the player and the protagonist, suggesting that the player is the true variable being tested.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"Community Theory\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm\",\"children\":\"The community theory suggests that Columbina is not a character but a system administrator — the only entity in the circus that understands its true purpose. Her three-loop storyline is not a narrative but a calibration process, testing whether the player can maintain consistency across iterations. The ending implies that the circus exists to test human memory and decision-making under repetition.\"}]]}],\"$L3\"]}]]}]}],\"$L4\"]}],[\"$L5\"],\"$L6\"]}],\"isPartial\":false,\"staleTime\":300,\"varyParams\":null,\"buildId\":\"TLbwCga2sWMTi4GXj34iv\"}\n3:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"FAQ\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"bg-surface-container border border-outline/20 p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-foreground mb-2\",\"children\":\"What happens if you make a mistake in Loop 2?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm\",\"children\":\"The game resets to Loop 1 without warning. You must start the three-loop sequence again from the beginning.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"bg-surface-container border border-outline/20 p-4\",